Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.71,0:00:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it around for me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.98,0:00:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.31,0:00:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you died, you'd survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.95,0:00:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Even unto a demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.68,0:00:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm {\i1}gambling{\i0} for fuck's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.66,0:00:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.66,0:00:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.88,0:00:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,ron
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.21,0:01:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure this is the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.21,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, you've only played Mahjong for a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.00,0:01:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Except you didn't deal into anyone's hand even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.14,0:01:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Call for Yagi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.08,0:01:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Even a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.74,0:01:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at last the{\i1} pro{\i0} arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.51,0:01:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki, having a hard time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.88,0:01:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ron
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.37,0:01:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond question.\NRyuzaki is simply no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.48,0:01:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The only concern now is this man
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.20,0:01:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi Keiji
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.77,0:01:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, we're 23,00 points behind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's already South hand 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.77,0:01:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:01:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh. Turning the game around at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.14,0:01:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to overextend quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.65,0:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Observing him for the rest of this East-South match is safest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:02:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.28,0:02:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why Yagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.28,0:02:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They say the kid's a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.28,0:02:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes him even more eerie as an unknown quantity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.48,0:02:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to not underestimate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.41,0:02:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,o-okay
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.38,0:02:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This man.\NDid he pick up on Akagi's talent with one glance?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.51,0:02:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more simply observing is more frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.17,0:02:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people would want to show off in a situation like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His restraint is admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.13,0:02:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in a different league than Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi Keiji
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.08,0:02:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With Yagi observing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.54,0:02:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he aims to find the way Akagi has taken first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,H-how did he sense that the previous player's Tenpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.34,0:03:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,JyunChan SanSyoku
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A middle 8 wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.51,0:03:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally he would discard an 8 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.05,0:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why therefore discard that other tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:04:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Chanta hands and these discards are tough to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more likely he'd think he'd deal into that hand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.22,0:04:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with the 5 Sou rather than the 8 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.08,0:04:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he trust his reads to this extent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.30,0:04:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what is this kid {\i1}seeing{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.04,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The three zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.40,0:04:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The left hand player's discards can be separated into three zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.22,0:04:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In these discards, the 6 Pin and 6 Man tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.45,0:04:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 3/2 Sou were discarded before the 3 Pin and 9 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.89,0:04:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore, the 3 Pin and 9 Sou were more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.42,0:04:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And this vicinity is a danger zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.85,0:04:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we then go into reading the hand itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.42,0:04:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The first 6 Pin discard removes the possibility of a Metanpin hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.14,0:04:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus he holds a Chanta hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.14,0:05:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And furthermore if you consider his discard of the 3 and 2 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.54,0:05:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a 7 8 9 SanSyoku remains in his hand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.08,0:05:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that case the North, 3 Sou and 2 Sou were unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's a Chanta hand, the 5 Man discarded on the 5th turn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.57,0:05:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,would suggest this had.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.62,0:05:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A slim possibility remains
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.91,0:05:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,delaying the discard of the 5 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.28,0:05:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end the left hand opponent's hand should look like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.62,0:05:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid has seen through this up to now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.54,0:05:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only does he seem to see through everyone's hands,\NHe has incredible luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The left hand player is in a position to simply crush Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.33,0:06:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Riitchi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.33,0:06:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This Richi off a 6 Pin discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the 4 Pin closed triplet is 100% profitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.05,0:06:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He may happen to draw another 4 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.80,0:06:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and achieve a Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.54,0:06:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus there's the chance of an additional Dora tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.14,0:06:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you think about it, declaring Riichi with instead a 5 Pin discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you get this hand. Infinitely better!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.11,0:06:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why on earth didn't he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.37,0:07:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.51,0:07:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's making mistakes characteristic of a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.37,0:07:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.37,0:07:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take advantage of that opening and destroy his game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Once he's off balance...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.37,0:07:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He's vunerable to a more able player.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Why's he smiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My god.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the bastard found a weakness?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.97,0:07:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.95,0:07:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi Ippatsu TanYao
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.42,0:07:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Five thousand two hundred points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.42,0:07:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done! First place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:07:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take your place, Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,p-please, Yagi.
