Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One more game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take first in one more game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My debts are entirely repaid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.51,0:09:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.91,0:09:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a little proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.91,0:09:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.11,0:09:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This Yagi guy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows all sorts of tricks and slight of hand, doesn't he.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.82,0:09:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.88,0:09:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When tiles are collected, and everyone stacks theirs,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.28,0:09:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi should stack afterwards from the remaining tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.51,0:09:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To protect against any cheating...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the very least we could ask for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.31,0:09:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.54,0:09:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasuoka, dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:10:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard this kid cheated from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.77,0:10:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We make a little deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.77,0:10:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.77,0:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mutually
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.77,0:10:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone is found cheating
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.62,0:10:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They lose an arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. As you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.34,0:10:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.68,0:10:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,W-wait
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.32,0:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And one further thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a request for you specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.63,0:10:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This contest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.17,0:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little unfair, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.61,0:11:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfair?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.61,0:11:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki is apt to lose a huge sum of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.97,0:11:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And as his rep player, my name is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.82,0:11:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I could lose my livelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you have to compare with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.48,0:11:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lose, only Nangou will be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.20,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't lose anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.97,0:11:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Our conditions are too different from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's simple. Let's make a personal wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.14,0:11:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,100,000 Yen for each East-South match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,100,000!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize that you can't get that kid of money right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm willing to accept a substitute for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A substitute?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:12:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,One finger for 100,000 Yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.00,0:12:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.71,0:12:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're playing a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.94,0:12:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.28,0:12:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.08,0:12:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. If it's the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We know I can't pay that huge sum.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you look a little suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not able to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.45,0:12:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you substitute a finger a well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.34,0:12:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If we say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.34,0:12:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.34,0:12:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.25,0:12:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,T-this is crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard's a top player.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.14,0:12:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.14,0:12:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped if he's a kid or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.54,0:12:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They tried to scare him and see what he'd do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.28,0:13:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan was to overwhelm him with pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The little bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.85,0:13:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He parried the Yakuza's threats elegantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.82,0:13:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got some balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.85,0:13:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Gambling changes fundamentally depending on whether you have something to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.08,0:13:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's nothing to lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or if there's nothing to gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.51,0:13:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,only one's intuition and guts are the deciding factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.45,0:13:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ability is paramount.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.45,0:13:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However if there is a large sum, or life at stake...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.37,0:13:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot win by ability alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.42,0:13:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how well you read your opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.42,0:13:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's meaningless if  you don't trust your own conclusions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:14:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You must entrust your fate to your decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.51,0:14:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means your will to trust yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Your soul itself is what is being tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.68,0:14:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A closed wait for a 7 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.48,0:14:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,With a hand like that\Nyou'd usually wait for a two sided wait before declaring Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.22,0:14:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastard. He wants to see how Akagi will react.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Now this is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, If I were Akagi, i'd think...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.97,0:15:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd turn discard of the 7 Man creates a safe zone,\Nsuggesting a 6 Man discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.74,0:15:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you're more faint of heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The 9 Sou safe tile discard is also a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But Akagi is Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.63,0:15:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is no normal war of nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He made the 6 Man pass
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.20,0:15:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But holds onto the wining tile, the 7 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.68,0:16:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And even under this pressue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusts his decisions, and never wavers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.97,0:16:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The 5 Man tile also passes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Seizing the game flow, this West first round belongs to Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At last!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(336.534,119.8)}* An Agari Hai is a tile that, upon discard, sets up your hand to win. It "tells" what your hand is waiting on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That 7 Sou is unmistakably an Agari-hai.*
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.54,0:16:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi's tenacity is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he loses dealer position
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.82,0:16:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He defies Akagi's reading of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do, Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.02,0:17:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to win this trash hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You may take the East hand one
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.94,0:17:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But in return you'll pick up some doubts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.80,0:17:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And those doubts in time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Will hit you hard, like a body blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.31,0:17:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you start questioning your own judgement
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You will seriously doubt yourself towards the end\NWhen the pressure's on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he's very likely to make a bad discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.22,0:17:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And that mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.22,0:17:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Can be fatal in a match like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.54,0:17:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,キターーー(゜∀゜)ーーーー!!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.60,0:17:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,RyanPeiKou Pinhu Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.48,0:17:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A Mangan hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.14,0:17:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,T-that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.25,0:17:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be odd for him to be waiting for that tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.45,0:18:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Could he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.40,0:18:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,PRICK
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.42,0:18:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He threw away a Mangan win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to confirm his own reads were correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.68,0:18:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mahjong game that could cost the loser a finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.97,0:18:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid. Doesn't he care what happens to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.31,0:18:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.31,0:18:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you show me your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in Tenpai, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.34,0:18:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:19:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A twisted way of playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.08,0:19:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Typical of someone who only ever thinks of tricking people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.11,0:19:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So unimaginative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.06,0:19:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi. You alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.11,0:19:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The game has only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,???????
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't gauge this kid's strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt this man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon become an absurdly good player.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.40,0:19:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.77,0:19:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But, right now I can beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I have grasped your weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't understand how Kan and Riichi really work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That IGNORANCE
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.94,0:19:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.82,0:19:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You declared Riichi by discarding the 6 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.68,0:19:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that moment if you discarded the 5 Pin instead
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The 4 Pin closed triplet is 100% better positioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.28,0:20:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In time if you draw another 4 Pin you may declare closed Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Kan there is the possibility of another Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But why didn't he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I dare say you thought you can't declare Kan during Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.22,0:20:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a misunderstanding indicative of beginners.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ignorance in declaring Kan during Riichi is that very thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That awesome Yaku called Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I will teach it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.77,0:20:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In East hand 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it ends without a winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.14,0:21:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Akagi is first to seize the game flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.57,0:21:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,White Yakuhai. 400/700 points. Honba count 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.28,0:21:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.17,0:21:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi, Tsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.71,0:21:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nomi*. 700/1,300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.71,0:21:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(355.947,87.6)}*Nomi: the state of a hand which contains only yaku and no dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.25,0:21:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if some common people are able to grasp the game flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.68,0:21:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they often can't take advantage of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.05,0:22:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.70,0:22:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the rate of game play becomes too great,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.94,0:22:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they become unnecessarily cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.05,0:22:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He breaks his own flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.25,0:22:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\i1}しかし{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.25,0:22:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi has no such limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.20,0:22:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.86,0:22:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentanpin, Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.17,0:22:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,One Dora. A Mangan win.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.17,0:22:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000/4,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.57,0:22:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,From the very start he's steadfast beyond imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.22,0:22:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His hands move without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.93,0:23:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.00,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.54,0:23:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi. Ippatsu. IttsuKan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And dealer payment. 12,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.14,0:23:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of South round 2, Akagi comes top.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.11,0:23:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,plus 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.82,0:23:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi is second with minus 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.74,0:23:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi hasn't yet made his move.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.46,0:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lost more points than he can,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.42,0:23:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so he uses a skillful trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.40,0:24:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the hand I've been waiting for!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.73,0:24:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the cheat known as the "Caterpillar"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.25,0:24:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And under it, Yagi's hand will undergo a {\i1}Metamorphosis{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.20,0:24:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he takes two 7 Sou tiles in his left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.00,0:24:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And pretending to push his own wall forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.60,0:24:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He pushes the 7 Sou tiles into the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.60,0:24:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The tiles basically mimic the motion of a caterpillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.60,0:24:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His final move is to return two tiles from the right edge in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.45,0:24:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Practiced many tens of thousands of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.42,0:24:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.42,0:24:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps that, at this point, everyone is focused on sorting their own tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.51,0:24:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In Yagi's hand movements, there is nothing to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.08,0:25:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Done like this, the two tiles returned to his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.85,0:25:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,merely ensure he has the correct number of tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.51,0:25:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important are the two he has placed in the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.15,0:25:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the Dora indicator,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.15,0:25:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other will be one in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.68,0:25:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, his garbage hand
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.09,0:25:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can transform into a monster hand with EIGHT dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.22,0:25:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.03,0:25:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,GOT HIM
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.91,0:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When he knows he won't deal into anyone's hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.85,0:26:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and can draw his winning tile he declares Riichi, even with a large lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.71,0:26:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,His reading is probably correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.65,0:26:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He has an innate sense for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.80,0:26:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,SHIKASHI, even this genius has a weak point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.85,0:26:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't number many,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.69,0:26:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have enough experience in Mahjong{\b1\i1} rough play{\b0\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.11,0:26:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And moreover,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.11,0:26:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know the {\i1\b1}terror{\i0\b0} of the Riichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.60,0:26:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to teach him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.60,0:26:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\b1\i1}Achilles Heel{\b0\i0} of the Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.60,0:26:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, Akagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.22,0:26:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We force you out so you can't draw your Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.31,0:26:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.34,0:27:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.27,0:27:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The game flow don't mean shit if you can't draw a tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.85,0:27:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.85,0:27:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, it's all in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.62,0:27:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.49,0:27:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.49,0:27:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what are you planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.08,0:27:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.68,0:27:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,GOT HIM!!!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.58,0:27:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.66,0:28:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,F-four Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.64,0:28:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,E-EIGHT DORA
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.84,0:28:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.72,0:28:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now do you understand the terror of the Riichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're declared Riichi, you're powerless to adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.02,0:28:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to any changes that may come later.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.02,0:28:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what he was aiming for?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.05,0:28:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know the terror of the Yaku called "Riichi."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.37,0:28:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A weakness characteristic of a novice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.25,0:28:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.42,0:28:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.40,0:29:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That 3 Pin is my winning tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.34,0:29:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.00,0:29:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You MUST discard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.08,0:29:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Rooooooohhhhnnn.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.28,0:29:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no ura-Dora, but 8 Dora, Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.94,0:29:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A Baiman win, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.57,0:29:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A 16,000 point direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.60,0:29:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns the game around!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.85,0:30:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A-akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.65,0:30:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.65,0:30:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be more direct now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.08,0:30:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi vs. Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.20,0:30:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At last the confrontation reaches its final act.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.17,0:30:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi with a 3,700 point lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.74,0:30:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and Akagi playing catchup after a reversal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.60,0:30:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one hand left, South hand 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.68,0:30:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a slow hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.68,0:30:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the potential for merely a Chinitsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.00,0:30:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not what he needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.51,0:31:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, a Tanpin would be best.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.91,0:31:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi's good with only a 1,000 point win.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.05,0:31:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got to keep pace with this bastard's speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.48,0:31:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.48,0:31:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the young genius
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.48,0:31:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,imagined an entirely different story based on this hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.45,0:31:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.34,0:31:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.05,0:31:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Agaki you little scamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.08,0:31:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi's trying to head Yagi off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.45,0:32:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to make them think he's going for a Chinitsu or Honitsu hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.20,0:32:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and tying the hands of the other players besides Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.22,0:32:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In this showdown,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.22,0:32:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have the balls to stay in the game,\Nand risk dealing him a winning tile in the last hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.05,0:32:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After he called tiles twice, they're only discarding safe tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.11,0:32:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.54,0:32:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.88,0:32:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like a Chinitsu hand, but there's no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.54,0:32:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he doesn't need that big of a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.34,0:32:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Those three calls are probably bluffs instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.48,0:32:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,More likely he's got a Tanyao.\NWith a single dora tile, he'll overtake my 4,000 point lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.94,0:33:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.97,0:33:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I , above all, can't discard this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.30,0:33:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling tiles three times,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.54,0:33:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's almost certainly in Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.82,0:33:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I delay, he has time to draw his winning tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.85,0:33:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. He hasn't realized Akagi's not in Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.28,0:33:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, I think this is on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.65,0:33:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the North tile Akagi discarded,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.82,0:33:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a hell wait since two North tiles have been discarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.62,0:33:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in this situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.68,0:33:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but still, no one will take the chance of discarding one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.60,0:33:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely, what Akagi is aiming at,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.25,0:33:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is a 3-way wait on 3 or 6 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.13,0:33:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.13,0:33:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,These remaining 4 Man tiles are damn strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.42,0:33:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there some {\i1}other{\i0} goal here?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.74,0:34:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.11,0:34:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why on earth did he declare Kan?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.94,0:34:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Forcing yourself to wait on a single tile
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.02,0:34:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of waiting on 3 is a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.17,0:34:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's put his own head in a noose.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.37,0:34:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't fucking believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.22,0:34:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.70,0:34:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting your hand slip while drawing a Rinshan Tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.94,0:35:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.88,0:35:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's without mistake in a naked wait for a Man tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.11,0:35:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.74,0:35:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.45,0:35:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,any tile but a Man tile is safe to discard!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.51,0:35:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even an extremely dangerous Dora tile, the 4 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.05,0:35:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he have such a calm demeanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.34,0:35:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And above all, why did he declare Kan?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.20,0:35:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there some reason why he threw away a 3 way wait for a single naked wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.81,0:35:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The 4 Sou Dora? But I'm sure I saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.99,0:35:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.99,0:35:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That 4 Man Kan was just a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.77,0:35:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,From Yagi's perspective it would look like a normal Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.53,0:35:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But to Akagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.80,0:36:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The 4 Sou Dora was hidden in the closed 4 Man Kan, like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.51,0:36:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When he drew his Rinshan replacement tile,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.48,0:36:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He deliberately knocked over his own tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.48,0:36:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and let his opponent see only the Man symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.46,0:36:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say, he made his opponent mistakenly believe he's in a single Man tile wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.85,0:36:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This turn that Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.02,0:36:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,would be impossible to discard because Akagi is going for a Tanyao hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.97,0:36:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an utterly dangerous tile!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.97,0:36:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in this turn only...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.51,0:37:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.88,0:37:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You realized your own mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.19,0:37:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such an Idiot, Yagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.57,0:37:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really believe in a match like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.00,0:37:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I would knock over my own tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.31,0:37:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't trust people so...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.24,0:37:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:37:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,TanYao with Two Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.22,0:38:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A reversal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.63,0:38:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-YAGI
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.34,0:38:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm SAVED.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.20,0:38:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.57,0:38:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Really. Because of you. I'm saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.45,0:38:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll never gamble again!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.45,0:38:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki-san. This isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.32,0:38:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the 3 million that erased Nangou's debt
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.80,0:38:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and play one more match with that at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.73,0:38:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Double or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.70,0:38:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, don't be reckless!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.51,0:38:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lose, it's my life on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.71,0:38:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.71,0:38:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already faced death once.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.71,0:38:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's push this to the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.61,0:39:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.68,0:39:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.68,0:39:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they're the ones feeling the most pressure at a double or nothing proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.05,0:39:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they've got no hopes of winning this game
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.91,0:39:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is what they're feeling most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.06,0:39:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never see such sitting ducks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.87,0:39:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can pluck them, pluck them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.48,0:39:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I never set eyes on this kid (???)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.51,0:39:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.85,0:39:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective! Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.20,0:39:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell you want!?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.20,0:39:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I-it won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.05,0:40:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell is this about?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.88,0:40:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.88,0:40:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.62,0:40:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.35,0:40:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enough that my life has been saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.66,0:40:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just please stop him for me already.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.97,0:40:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.13,0:40:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.13,0:40:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the "chicken run" survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.88,0:40:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not really my nephew!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.88,0:40:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I know all about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.31,0:40:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.31,0:40:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see him play Mahjong a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.85,0:40:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, in a Chicken Run contest,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.40,0:40:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand why people can't do it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.11,0:40:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.22,0:40:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a contest on a sea cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.28,0:40:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who can do it, go off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.08,0:40:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, don't rashly apply the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.74,0:40:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Done cleanly the probability of survival is high.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.97,0:40:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,T-then he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.87,0:41:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't brake at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.87,0:41:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But if that's the case, he had no hope of escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.91,0:41:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, the little bastard made that decision, and put his heart and soul into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.91,0:41:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight I confirmed it by watching that kid's Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.37,0:41:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At whatever moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.54,0:41:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've observed his ability to make trustworthy decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.08,0:41:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with an unwavering heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.05,0:41:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability to trust one's own decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.27,0:41:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's him to a T. Akagi Shigeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.74,0:41:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Detective. Just wait a..
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.34,0:41:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.74,0:41:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Weak men unavoidably will fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.17,0:41:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi knows this instinctively.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.05,0:42:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.80,0:43:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.86,0:43:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi, Ippatsu, Chitoitsu, Ura Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.77,0:43:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.00,0:43:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If I discard the 3 Man or 6 Man I'm in Tenpai,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.34,0:43:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little risky, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.65,0:43:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I-f I stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.02,0:44:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,T-this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.80,0:44:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't expecting to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.59,0:44:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.57,0:44:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi, Ippatsu, 3 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.40,0:44:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You look dizzy, Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.80,0:44:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.80,0:44:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He drew and discarded that 2 Man when he declared Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.34,0:44:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though I defended against it above all (???)
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.74,0:44:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He deliberately chose a single 1 Man wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.60,0:44:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi has begun to break.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.20,0:45:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.02,0:45:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinhu, one Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.28,0:45:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.20,0:45:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi is starting to grasp the fundamental principles of competitive Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.80,0:45:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.42,0:45:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahjong is not about how to win your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.68,0:45:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is about how to deny your opponents theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.60,0:46:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Only those who can expand their own vision can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.74,0:46:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.37,0:46:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentanpin, 3 Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.65,0:47:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.51,0:47:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry but I don't have the money on me right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.27,0:47:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow I'll contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.20,0:47:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.12,0:47:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi-san. It's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.82,0:47:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Double or nothing with the three million we just won.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.71,0:47:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the game's wager is six million.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.67,0:47:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,D-DOUBLE OR NOTHING!?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.05,0:47:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi. Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.67,0:47:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let it end here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.00,0:47:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We keep going to the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.48,0:47:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Until one of us falls apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.68,0:47:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,AKAGI
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.68,0:47:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.68,0:47:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do it another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.68,0:47:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.68,0:48:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be best to officially hold the rematch on another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.17,0:48:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can ask a boss I know to supervise the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.42,0:48:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of money at risk here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.54,0:48:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That way there will be no tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.65,0:48:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh. Don't worry about it kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.65,0:48:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The best stage for you to play on,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.14,0:48:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I will provide.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.05,0:48:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki. That's right, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.97,0:48:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.42,0:49:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi. You showed us some pretty interesting Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.07,0:49:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.07,0:49:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you think it over just once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.14,0:49:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.25,0:49:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enough that you've saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.28,0:49:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to get into a dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.37,0:49:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest is not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.06,0:49:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, then at least
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.91,0:49:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just bet the three million we won today.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.54,0:49:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what we won.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.20,0:49:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we bet my life again for 3 million my sanity can't take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.57,0:49:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.57,0:49:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.57,0:50:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best not to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.82,0:50:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What intimidates them is our Madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.51,0:50:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The conviction to not apply the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.11,0:50:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And that time too I didn't brake at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.05,0:50:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I thought that was the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.77,0:50:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.05,0:50:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In that Chicken Run where you went off the cliff,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.40,0:50:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you had no intention of braking from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.02,0:50:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what saved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.64,0:50:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought that beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.64,0:50:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not to brake,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.64,0:50:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather the reverse, stepping on the accelerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.32,0:50:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That was your chance for victory, wasn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.71,0:50:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do something like that with only a {\i1}chance{\i0} of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.88,0:50:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight's goal was only Nangou's.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.94,0:50:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,W-what did I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.40,0:51:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Betting your life on a Mahjong game.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.02,0:51:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No one with an ordinary nerve could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.37,0:51:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.42,0:51:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"That time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.42,0:51:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't forgotten, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.80,0:51:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the first time I saw Nangou playing Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.28,0:51:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When it was about to end,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.28,0:51:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That Sansyouku winning hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.19,0:51:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that 5 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.19,0:51:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the most dangerous tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.10,0:51:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm {\b1\i1}gambling{\b0\i0} for fuck's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.60,0:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That itself was just "stepping on the accelerator."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.82,0:51:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not something that can be done with any normal nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.55,0:51:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting your soul to Madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.22,0:51:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we see if we can avoid it one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.51,0:52:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With Madness of the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.30,0:52:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The madness of the soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.45,0:52:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujiya-san. It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.65,0:52:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,8 Sou.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.28,0:53:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(160.075,186.8)}Fukumoto Sensei-->
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.51,0:53:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.37,0:53:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That Yagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.74,0:53:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. he's a wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.37,0:53:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.74,0:53:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's someone you easily take lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.71,0:53:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's involved with that crooked cop, Yasuoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.74,0:53:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very likely that Yasuoka
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.74,0:53:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is involved with the Nagauti gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.25,0:53:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So then our Miyoti group is involved
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.57,0:53:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we entrusted you with our power.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.00,0:53:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.94,0:53:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.94,0:53:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Fujiyosi
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.94,0:53:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding the amazing master
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.02,0:53:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That master is just now in a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.00,0:54:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.94,0:54:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.71,0:54:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chuuren Poutou. A Yakuman win.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.08,0:56:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly eight million.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.65,0:56:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,EIGHT MILLION!?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.74,0:56:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All I have to do is beat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.74,0:56:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I got it. We'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.74,0:56:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.62,0:56:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.37,0:56:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You little bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.02,0:56:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.37,0:57:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.37,0:57:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.77,0:57:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's come.
